main event: On May 30, 1949, observers in El Paso, Texas, reported seeing a highly reflective oblong object while watching a fighter aircraft.
interesting points: The object was first observed while watching a fighter plane,It was highly reflective and measured about one inch long,Direction of the object was from overhead to east by north east,The object disappeared into clouds after three minutes of observation,No sound or odor was detected from the object.
witness description: PFC Lewis Liska and Pvt William Tyrrel, both in military service.
